The paper deals with the classification of simple games based on axioms and computability, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). It also involves the use of algorithms and finite carriers, which are topics in data structures (cs.DS) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also touches upon the concept of computability, which is a topic in both computational complexity (cs.CC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
